              1.93 (0.75 to 4.97)) prior to sex had a higher STI
              prevalence.Conclusions The higher prevalence of STIs among PWH
              with unhealthy alcohol use who have partners on PrEP suggests
              that this subgroup may be a high-yield focus for targeted
